---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Qatar Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/qatar/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
  { title: 'Bahrain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahrain' },
  { title: 'Saudi Arabia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/saudi-arabia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'qatarFit', header: 'Qatar Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'QAR 1,400-2,000/mo', qatarFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'QAR 1,650-2,350/mo', qatarFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'QAR 1,300-1,850/mo', qatarFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'QAR 1,200-1,700/mo', qatarFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Qatar Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'QAR 500-1,500/mo', qatarFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'QAR 1,300-2,000', annual: 'QAR 15,600-24,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'QAR 1,800-2,700', annual: 'QAR 21,600-32,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'QAR 2,400-3,600', annual: 'QAR 28,800-43,200' },
  { category: 'Qatar Public (Hamad)', monthly: 'Subsidized for residents', annual: 'Small fees' },
  { category: 'Qatar Private Clinic', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'QAR 300-800/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Qatar 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Qatar. World-class healthcare, tax-free living, modern infrastructure, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Qatar"
  subheadline="Qatar offers world-class healthcare, modern infrastructure, and tax-free living in a wealthy Gulf state—with property ownership pathways for residence."
  heroImage="/images/countries/qatar-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Qatar</h2>
  <p>
    Qatar combines Gulf wealth with improving quality of life—world-class healthcare, modern infrastructure, tax-free income, and safety. The 2022 World Cup drove massive infrastructure development. For wealthy retirees seeking sun and excellent healthcare without income tax, Qatar delivers.
  </p>

  <p>
    Doha provides cosmopolitan living with museums (Museum of Islamic Art, National Museum), dining, and international amenities. The Pearl-Qatar offers waterfront lifestyle. Al Khor and other areas provide quieter options. Everything is within easy reach in this small country.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; world-class facilities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English widely used</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> QAR 15,000-35,000/month (~$4,100-9,600); high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Desert; extremely hot summers (40°C+)</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax; no capital gains tax</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Among world's safest countries</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Qatar's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Qatar's healthcare is excellent—Hamad Medical Corporation operates public hospitals with modern facilities and international staff. Sidra Medicine (built by Qatar Foundation) is world-class for women and children. Private hospitals like American Hospital add options.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is heavily subsidized for residents. Expats typically have insurance through employers, but retirees need private coverage. Quality rivals the best anywhere—many doctors are Western-trained. No concerns about healthcare quality in Qatar.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Mandatory Health Insurance</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Qatar requires health insurance for all residents. The national health insurance system (Seha) is being implemented. Expats must have coverage that meets government standards. International insurance from major providers typically qualifies.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Qatar offers limited but improving options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Buying property in designated areas (The Pearl, Lusail) grants residence. Investment of QAR 730,000+ (approximately $200,000) provides 5-year renewable residence for buyer and family.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Qatar offers permanent residence to select individuals who've contributed to Qatar. Not commonly available to retirees but possible for those with exceptional connections or contributions.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Sponsorship</h3>
  <p>
    If you have adult children working in Qatar who meet income requirements, they may be able to sponsor parents. This depends on employer policies and sponsor income level.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Qatar:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mandatory:</strong> Health insurance required for all residents</li>
    <li><strong>Property visa:</strong> Insurance required for residence approval</li>
    <li><strong>Local options:</strong> Age limits often apply to Qatar insurers</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Usually best option for seniors</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Qatar</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for seniors—local Qatari insurers often have age restrictions. Major international providers (Cigna, BUPA, Allianz) are recognized and meet government requirements. Qatar's healthcare is excellent; ensure your plan covers local hospitals including Hamad Medical Corporation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Qatar, international providers without age restrictions work best:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Qatar</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Recognized in Qatar, good local network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Middle East focus, good local knowledge</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive regional pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers recognized in Qatar.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Qatar are moderate given excellent healthcare:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Qatar care is excellent; high deductible for major needs</li>
    <li><strong>Gulf-only coverage:</strong> Excluding Europe/US reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Hamad subsidy:</strong> Public hospitals are subsidized for residents</li>
    <li><strong>No tax offset:</strong> No income tax means full costs but no tax burden</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Property Investor, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,500/month pension. Buying QAR 1.5M apartment at The Pearl.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Property provides residence. Cigna Global for comprehensive coverage including US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~QAR 1,700/month (~$465). Tax-free pension goes far; excellent healthcare access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Children work in Qatar. Family sponsorship. Combined pension £3,500/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Sponsored by children. BUPA Global for both. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~QAR 4,200/month combined (~£920). Near family; excellent healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Indian Professional, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Former Qatar worker, now retired. Bought property. Pension + savings.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Property residence. Now Health regional coverage. Uses Hamad for routine care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~QAR 1,400/month (~$385). Familiar with Qatar; excellent lifestyle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Qatar without buying property?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Difficult. Qatar doesn't have a retirement visa. Main pathways are: property ownership in designated areas, family sponsorship from working children, or exceptional circumstances. Pure financial independence without property or family connection isn't a standard pathway.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How hot are Qatar summers?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very hot—40-50°C (104-122°F) in summer. Humidity adds to discomfort. Most expats stay indoors during summer days; outdoor activities are dawn/dusk or winter only. Everything is air-conditioned. Many Qatar expats travel during summer months to escape heat.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Qatar conservative for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderately. Qatar is more relaxed than Saudi Arabia. Alcohol available at hotels/restaurants (for non-Muslims with permits). Dress code is modest but not strict—no shorts in malls, swimwear at beaches/pools only. Ramadan requires public daytime discretion. Generally comfortable for Western retirees.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Qatar healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—among the best in the Middle East. Hamad Medical Corporation is world-class. Sidra Medicine (women's and children's) is cutting-edge. Many doctors are US/UK trained. Equipment is modern. You won't lack for quality healthcare in Qatar.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers recognized for Qatar residence.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Qatari authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
